# Nourish — AI Meal Planner

**Product:** User sets diet preferences + what's in the fridge → get a 5-day meal plan (breakfast, lunch, snack, dinner per day) with recipes and a consolidated shopping list. Target: busy professionals. Tagline: "Plan once. Eat well."

## Tech stack

- **Framework:** React 18 + TypeScript, Vite
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Routing:** React Router v6
- **Server state:** TanStack Query (meal plan from API)
- **AI:** Google Gemini API (gemini-2.0-flash) via Vercel API route — never expose API key in frontend
- **Persistence:** localStorage for last plan + shopping checked state
- **Deploy:** Vercel

## Tailwind (quick reference)

- **What it is:** Style via utility classes on `className` (no separate CSS files). One class = one concern (e.g. `flex`, `p-4`, `text-ink`).
- **Design tokens:** In `tailwind.config.js`, extend `theme` with the blueprint palette so you get `bg-paper`, `text-ink`, `border-accent`, `text-muted`, `bg-cream`, `bg-accent`, `bg-accent2`, etc. Map `--ink`, `--paper`, `--cream`, `--accent`, `--accent2`, `--muted`, `--border` from the design.
- **Frequently used:** Layout — `flex`, `flex-col`, `items-center`, `justify-between`, `gap-2` / `gap-4`. Grid — `grid`, `grid-cols-2`, `grid-cols-4`. Spacing — `p-4`, `px-4`, `mb-4`, `mt-2`. Typography — `font-serif` (Playfair), `font-mono` (labels), `text-sm` / `text-lg`. Responsive — `md:grid-cols-2`, `sm:flex-row`.
- **Purge-safe:** Use complete class names in JSX. Avoid `` `text-${color}` ``; use a mapping or full names (e.g. `text-ink`, `text-accent`) so Tailwind’s content scan keeps the classes.

## User flow (4 screens)

1. **Preferences** — Diet style chips, allergy/avoid chips, fridge ingredient grid (toggle what you have), max cook time. Generate button triggers plan generation.
2. **Kitchen scan** — Same screen: tag fridge items; Nourish uses these first (fewer items to buy).
3. **Plan (Your Week)** — 5 days (Mon–Fri), 4 meals per day. Day tabs. Each meal card: name, prep time, calories, fridge items used. Click meal → RecipeModal (ingredients + steps). "View Shopping List" → next screen.
4. **Shopping list** — Grouped by category (Produce, Protein, Dairy, Pantry, Grains). Checkbox per item; progress bar; persist checked state in localStorage. Export to clipboard, "Back to Plan".

